[ProgramSlugUrl] Change 'add file with applicant id' route to use program slug  (#11031)

### Description

As part of #10763, we want to use the program slug instead of program id
for all program URLs on the applicant side. This PR is changes
`/applicants/:applicantId/programs/:programId/blocks/:blockId/addFile/:inReview`
to
`/applicants/:applicantId/programs/:programParam/blocks/:blockId/addFile/:inReview`

PR changes:
1. Update the route in `server/conf/routes` to receive a `programParam`
string that can be the id or slug
2. Update edit method in
`server/app/controllers/applicant/ApplicantRoutes.java`
3. Update edit method in
`server/app/controllers/applicant/ApplicantProgramBlocksController.java`
to:
- Redirect home when feature is enabled and the program param could be a
slug but it's actually the program id (numeric)
- Get the latest program id corresponding to the program param, and
continue with existing functionality
4. Update tests to pass `programParam` and `isFromUrl` instead of only
`programId`
5. Add new tests

-    std::__1::chrono::steady_clock::time_point lastFrameTime = std::chrono::steady_clock::now();

pull_request.title: Fix email-validator dependency for Render deployment
pull_request.body:
Fixes the deployment failure on Render caused by missing email-validator dependency.

## Problem
The backend application was failing to deploy on Render with the following error:
```
ImportError: email-validator is not installed, run `pip install pydantic[email]`
```

This occurred because the `email-validator` package was listed in `requirements.txt` without a version specification, which can cause installation issues in certain deployment environments.

## Solution
Added explicit version specification `==2.2.0` to the `email-validator` dependency in `backend/requirements.txt`. This ensures:

- Consistent installation across all environments (local, CI/CD, and deployment)
- Proper support for Pydantic's `EmailStr` validation used in user schemas
- Reliable deployment on Render and other platforms

## Changes
- Updated `backend/requirements.txt`: Changed `email-validator` to `email-validator==2.2.0`

## Verification
-  Fresh environment installation works correctly
-  EmailStr validation functions properly with valid/invalid emails
-  No regression in existing functionality
-  UserCreate schema with email validation works as expected

This minimal change resolves the deployment issue while maintaining all existing functionality.
